  "evidence_excerpts": [
    {
      "text": "Last edit almost 3 years ago by svayambhu108\n\n201\n92 It was done by my right brain employing some kind of analogic processessing. It resembles the way the \"I Ching\" works. Synchronicity - which may be why I got so involved in the \"I Ching.\" not only did the high-speed forward of the inner tape de-synchronize stimulus + response + so misphase them. But the a priori inner analog was activated in time (i.e. soon enough) + it contained information - in fact instructions of what to do - which the ext",
      "matched_alias": "Ching",
      "term_id": "TERM_ching",
      "term_name": "Ching",
      "term_slug": "ching"
    },
    {
      "text": "Last edit almost 3 years ago by svayambhu108\n202\nNeeds Review\n202\n593 develop superior problem-solving abilities; i.e. to evolve. Valis is the system (which as I say, had to make adjustments when I solved the Xerox missive problem, especially in view of how I solved it). However there is a danger to the ecosphere in this a priori prior (foresighted) knowledge. The balance is jeopardized (for the reasons I give above). nonetheless this type of wisdom is that which both the O.T. + Zoroaster assign",
      "matched_alias": "Teilhard",
      "term_id": "TERM_teilhard",
      "term_name": "Teilhard",
      "term_slug": "teilhard"
    }
  ],
